					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-149-de</guid>
				<title>SCP-149-DE</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-149-de</link>
				<description>

&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;scp-image-block block-right&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://scp-wiki-de.wdfiles.com/local--files/scp-149-de/SCP-Geist.jpg&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot; alt=&quot;SCP-Geist.jpg&quot; class=&quot;image&quot; /&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;scp-image-caption&quot; style=&quot;width:300px;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-149-DE-A in its first encounter with Mobile Task Force DE4-𝔎.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Item #:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-149-DE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object Class:&lt;/strong&gt; Euclid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Containment Procedures:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-149-DE may not be opened or entered without the authorization of at least two O4 members. Should entry be necessary, a small storage marquee is to be erected on the ground above SCP-149-DE where the opening will be made under the guise of pedologic studies. This measure serves the avoidance of eyewitnesses. Complete public exclusion is impossible due to SCP-149-DE’s location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personnel are to enter SCP-149-DE unarmed and without ballistic protection equipment. Radio contact is required to be maintained at all times. When subjects are within SCP-149-DE, at least 10 fully armed guards are to be positioned at the exit. Should radio contact be lost or when it becomes otherwise evident that the personnel in SCP-149-DE were compromised by SCP-149-DE-A, all guards must keep their weapons ready to terminate all individuals emerging from the structure. All personnel that entered SCP-149-DE are to be subjected to a thorough psychological evaluation. Should corruption by SCP-149-DE be detected, the affected individuals are to be classified as class E personnel and to be quarantined until further notice. The opening in SCP-149-DE is to be fully closed and concealed following the completion of all tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Currently, SCP-149-DE-A is safely contained inside SCP-149-DE and does not require further containment efforts. If an expedition into SCP-149-DE becomes necessary, SCP-149-DE-A is not to be touched under any circumstance. Means of evading SCP-149-DE-A’s attention remain unknown. Once SCP-149-DE has been entered, it is advised to move as fast as possible. Should SCP-149-DE-A be sighted, the expedition force must return to the missions starting point, regardless of SCP-149-DE-A being in pursuit. Remote surveillance via drones, cameras, and microphones is not advised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A disinformation campaigns has to maintain the belief that SCP-149-DE was filled completely and can no longer be entered. Surveillance of SCP-149-DE is carried out via locally rented apartments. Should unauthorized parties try to gain access to SCP-149-DE, they are to be detained and interrogated. In case of an attack, the surrounding Foundation sites are to be informed and available troops are to be deployed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Public or private efforts to build upon SCP-149-DE are to be destroyed or prevented by all means.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-149-DE designates the remains of the Führerbunker in Berlin. Against openly available facts SCP-149-DE is still accessible and in better shape, even though all its entrances have been sealed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-149-DE possesses three anomalous properties. The concrete SCP-149-DE was built from is notably harder and more solid than any other known kind of concrete. This concrete has shown no signs of aging or erosion since Foundation acquisition, presumably because of its second property to repair any damage done to it within seconds. The third property of SCP-149-DE is its apparent ability to prevent SCP-149-DE-A from leaving the structure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-149-DE-A is a class II&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-286641-1&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;incorporeal humanoid entity which is seemingly trapped within SCP-149-DE. It possesses a horned head similar to a cow skull, a short tail, and a transparent black muscular body. It continuously drips a tar-like substance. This substance vanishes upon contact with matter, which has rendered collection unfeasible. The size of SCP-149-DE-A has never been accurately determined but is estimated to be 190&amp;#160;cm. Due to the topography of SCP-149-DE and the aggressive demeanor of SCP-149-DE-A, very little data is available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During previous expeditions into SCP-149-DE, SCP-149-DE-A was observed to either walk through the corridors of the bunker or sit on a chair, although this behavior was only noted during the first expedition. On all other missions, SCP-149-DE was encountered seemingly searching for the expedition troops, supporting the theory that SCP-149-DE-A is able to detect humans within SCP-149-DE. Attempts to surveil SCP-149-DE-A with drones and cameras failed because it immediately seeks out such devices when no humans are present in SCP-149-DE. How the entity affects electronics is unknown but cameras affected by it only show heavily distorted footage with occasional insertions of national socialist symbols. After becoming affected by SCP-149-DE, microphones only record continuous screaming, stemming from several persons. Software used for voice analysis found a match for individual voices with those of Joseph Goebbels, Hans Krebs and Adolf Hitler. &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;What relation those persons have to SCP-149-DE-A is unknown at this time.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-149-DE behaves in a hostile manner towards living humans and attacks every subject that enters its field of vision. SCP-149-DE-A passes through all materials without resistance except walls, ceilings, floors and doors of SCP-149-DE and is therefore unable to cause physical damage. Should it touch a subject, it will stiffen while its personality is radically restructured. Those afflicted gain a worldview strongly impacted by racism, antisemitism, anti-communism, and social Darwinism as well as a great hatred against the victorious powers of the Second World War and become extremely willing to resort to violence. Subjects are from this point on driven to create and propagate a national socialist fundamental order on a global scale. To this end, they use every available means. Since intelligence and memories of the afflicted remain unchanged, sometimes a thorough psychological evaluation is required because subjects often pretend to have not been affected by SCP-149-DE-A’s properties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-folded&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;collapsible-block-link&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;&gt;Interview&amp;nbsp;with&amp;nbsp;a&amp;nbsp;SCP-149-DE-A&amp;nbsp;subject&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-unfolded&quot; style=&quot;display:none&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-unfolded-link&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;collapsible-block-link&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;&gt;Close&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-content&quot;&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Foreword:&lt;/strong&gt; Agent Reiter has been a member of MTF DE4-𝔎 „PSI-Corps”&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-286641-2&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; and had been attacked by SCP-149-DE-A on the first expedition into SCP-149-DE. Her squad members escaped unscathed according to the results of the psychological evaluation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Agent Reiter is brought into the interrogation room by two guards and sits on the provided chair. The guards then chain her to the table. Dr. Stier enters as well and sits down opposed to Agent Reiter.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Begin Log.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; Good morning, how are you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; I waste away in a white cell here and have to endure the fuss of you doctors every day. How do you think I feel? I am healthy. Never felt better!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; That is debatable&amp;#8230; You are aware that you had a radical personality shift, are you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; You call it personality shift, I call it enlightenment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; Enlightenment? Interesting, about what were you enlightened?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; This world is squalid, Doctor. To many screwed up genes in this world, they are the root of all evils that ail humanity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; What do you think to do against it? Can something be done against it?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; Yes, of course you can do something against it. Sort out those with inferior genes and eradicate them with root and branch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; How would you determine who the ones possessing good genes are?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; As a first step I would use the genealogy. Much bad blood can be traced back to certain races. Afterward, modern methods can be used to create humans with superior genetics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier&lt;/strong&gt; Races? Which one would be the one that you would choose?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; That would be the Aryans. They are vastly superior to other races.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; And all other races should be eradicated?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; Yeah.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; Agent Reiter, you are aware that your husband is from Hungary, right? He is a Slav. You married him two years ago.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; Yes, greatest failure of my life but I didn’t know any better back then. Thank god we didn’t have children. I will get to the divorce immediately once I am out of here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; You spoke about the world being intervened by bad genes. Do you wish to enforce your agenda everywhere?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; Of course, otherwise, this bane would return over and over again.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; You know that the world would not be willing to let that happen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; Then we have to convince it. And who we cannot convince, we have to force.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; Would you go so far as to start a war. Like, a really big one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; Yes, as big as he has to be.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; You are aware that this is the ideology of the Nazis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; Yes. I can see that you aren’t thrilled but is it my fault that those assholes called Allies vilified the Nazis? They had the right idea!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; I know what you are getting at and I oppose it with all my being. But tell me one thing. Why did you tell me all this so freely? Had you kept silent you could have waited until more people got attacked SCP-149-DE-A to gain more allies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;#8230;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; Mrs Reiter?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agent Reiter:&lt;/strong&gt; I think you are right but&amp;#8230; It just wants out, you know? If I can’t convince you then I want you at least to listen to me. I don’t know why&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Stier:&lt;/strong&gt; Hm. I think we are done here for now.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ende des Logs.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Remarks:&lt;/strong&gt; Agent Reiter was classified as Class E personnel and was placed under surveillance. The subject still attempts to propagate her ideology to anyone who listens to her. Others affected by SCP-149-DE showed less openness and are often secretive. Although unknown, it is regarded as probable that constitutes the result of a learning process of SCP-149-DE-A. Resulting assumptions about SCP-149-DE-A possessing a telepathic to its victims are regarded as &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: line-through;&quot;&gt;un&lt;/span&gt;confirmed &amp;#8212;at this time (See Incident 149-DE-1). At the moment, research to sever this link is underway but is so far unsuccessful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discovery:&lt;/strong&gt; The Foundation became aware of SCP-149-DE upon discovering documents from &lt;a href=&quot;http://scp-int.wikidot.com/skp-portal&quot;&gt;the SKP&lt;/a&gt; in a hidden safe during a sweep of an abandoned facility of &lt;a href=&quot;http://scp-int.wikidot.com/abteilung-xxv-hub&quot;&gt;Section XXV&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-folded&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;collapsible-block-link&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;&gt;Selected&amp;nbsp;documentation&amp;nbsp;of&amp;nbsp;the&amp;nbsp;SKP&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-unfolded&quot; style=&quot;display:none&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-unfolded-link&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;collapsible-block-link&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;&gt;Close&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-content&quot;&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;font-family: Old English Text MT&quot;&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SKP-Station ███████, Berlin, the ██/██/1940&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Research Report 89/2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the course of researching new construction materials we managed a great break-through. We succeeded in creating a concrete mixture that repels all damaging substances tested so far and pulls particles beneficial for strength and stability from the air and like this, strengthens itself further and further. In this way an extremely durable and resilient concrete is created over time that is already on par with common concretes upon pouring. This special wears the name &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Adamas Concrete&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SKP Headquarter, Kassel, the 01/19/1943&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Approval Adamas/1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Führer ordered the construction of a new air-raid shelter yesterday that has to ensure the safety of himself as well as the leadership. Because the Adamas Concrete passed all test runs until now, Himmler proposed it as the base material of the bunker. I hereby approve the use of the Adamas Concrete for the construction of the Führerbunker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Obersturmbannführer Schön&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further documentation regarding the composition and production of the &amp;quot;Adamas Concrete&amp;quot; was recovered. The Foundation has already created the first prototypes. Test results are still being compiled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Initially, an expedition into SCP-149-DE was put on hold because it was unknown in what form Section XXV had used the building and an unnecessary loss of personnel should be prevented until further information was available. On ██.██.2013 Research Team 25 managed the restoration of the documents, followed by the planning and execution of the first expedition, followed by a psychological evaluation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-folded&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;collapsible-block-link&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;&gt;Restored&amp;nbsp;documentation&amp;nbsp;of&amp;nbsp;Section&amp;nbsp;XXV&amp;nbsp;regarding&amp;nbsp;SCP-149-DE&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-unfolded&quot; style=&quot;display:none&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-unfolded-link&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;collapsible-block-link&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;&gt;Close&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;collapsible-block-content&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#8230;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#8230;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#8230;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#8230;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#8230;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&amp;#8230;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ERROR: DATA CORRUPTED BY UNAUTHORIZED ACCESS.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;RESTORING DATA.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 06/ 01/ 1959&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Research Assignment 67/1&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;The rumors regarding the Führerbunker triggered cause for curiosity in some party functionaries. Section XXV has gained the mission to examine the building and got information of the dismantled SKP for this reason. For this task a 15 men crew has been assembled. The list of the participants is attached to this document.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Officer Konstantin Mader&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 05/ 10/ 1959&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Research Report Assignment &amp;quot;Führerbunker&amp;quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;The first analysis has concluded. The concrete of the building is of astounding quality and calibre but the Magisters &lt;a href=&quot;http://scp-int.wikidot.com/SCP-089-DE&quot;&gt;Eisen&lt;/a&gt; think they discovered a consciousness inside the ruins. Further information is attached to this report.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Head of Operations Nickolas Heitz&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 05/ 11/ 1959&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Destroy Order 45/B&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;It is to be assumed that this here is are remains from NS times. It is either to be removed for a close examination and subsequent destruction or, if that is not possible, to be destroyed on the spot. Our Sowjet Friends shall not gain the impression we would indulge in our NS past. The start of Operation Exorzismus&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-286641-3&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; is hereby ordered. In case of emergency, use&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Officer Konstantin Mader&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 05/ 21/ 1959&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Project report for Operation Exorzismus&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;According to Magister Eisen, the consciousness seems not to be a deliberate creation of the Nazi Regime. Apparently, the concrete not only absorbed material but also emotions from the inhabitants and created&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;with them. An analysis is currently carried out on-site to facilitate a proper destruction. Also requesting additional security staff because the subject&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;seems to influence personnel inside the bunker.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Head of Operations Nickolas Heitz&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 06/ 04/ 1959&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Project Report for Operation Exorzismus&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;The consciousness extends over the entire bunker and seems Not-&lt;/tt&gt;[DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;slowly but steadily. To remove the mindset a thorough reeducation will be necessary. Additionally,&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;removing it completely from the ruins is time consuming.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Head of Operations Nickolas Heitz&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 06/ 06/ 1959&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Operation Report for Operation Exorzismus&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;An unforeseen complication occured.&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;seems to have changed its defense strategy. The Führerbunker starts to rebuild itself slowly. Maybe, a massive shock, an explosion like the Soviet Union&#039;s blasting operations could abort the process,&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;Working on counter measures. Further information is attached to this document.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 10/ 04/ 1959&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Operation Instructions for Operation Exorzismus&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;The proposed blasting is authorized. It cannot be allowed that this symbol of our shame remains.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Officer Konstantin Mader&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 06/ 30/ 1959&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Operation Report for Operation Exorzismus&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;After evaluating the collected data is can be assumed that&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;still exists. Our know-how in this area is not sufficient for now. Proposing to start a new attempt in the future although the problem is under control for now.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Magister Eisen&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 05/ 07/ 1988&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Reactivation of Operation Exorzismus&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;The Party is planning to build new residential buildings near and on the Führerbunker. To ensure the safety of the inhabitants the reactivation of Operation Exorzismus is hereby ordered. Magister Flamm takes over the supervision.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Officer Konstantin Mader&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 05/ 12/ 1988&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Operation Report for Operation Exorzismus&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;The progress regarding&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;from the late Magister Eisen are helpful in identifying and deleting&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;The demolition of the outer walls can be carried out shortly. However, it seems&lt;/tt&gt; [DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;has changed with the years. They are way more complex and reactive.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Magister Flamm&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 05/ 25/ 1988&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Operation Report for Operation Exorzismus&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[DATA CORRUPTED] &lt;tt&gt;cannot be removed further with our current know-how, for the most part because we can no longer get close to its body. But the bunker has been decontaminated far enough to remove everything except for the basements. I advise against filling the remains, because the workers [DATA CORRUPTED] {{This could have unforeseen consequences for its victims. Nonetheless, I and several other Magisters can assure that it cannot leave the remains of the Führerbunker due to our barrier.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Magister Flamm&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Berlin, the 05/ 28/ 1988&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Ministry for State Security&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;Section XXV&lt;/tt&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Discontinuation of Operation Exorzismus.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;This degree of removal is completely sufficient for the Party. Operation Exorzismus is hereby suspended.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: right;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Signed: Officer Konstantin Mader&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;DATA RESTORATION COMPLETE&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;DR. HOFFMANN HAS RECEIVED AN ELECTRONIC MESSAGE. THE LOST DATA WILL BE RESTORED SHORTLY.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
